main event: A witness observed a pale pink, amber-lit object in the sky over Stone Harbor, New Jersey for about 15 minutes in October 1966.
interesting points: The object appeared to be about 200 feet in diameter and the size of a jet aircraft in the sky.
The object moved in a southwest, northwest, and then south direction towards the witness.
The object had a slightly swaying motion and the lights were in the shape of a triangle.
There was no sound associated with the object.
The witness had just finished playing a game of soccer when they observed the object.
